tuning. Our study of a hearing gene in bats strongly implicates\n              Prestin\n              in the evolution of echolocation, and suggests independent evolution of high-frequency hearing in bats. These results highlight the potential problems of extracting phylogenetic signals from functional genes that may be prone to convergence.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Li, Gang", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Wang, Jinhong", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Rossiter, Stephen J.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Jones, Gareth", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Cotton, James A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Zhang, Shuyi", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/9e1f7151b898965cbc6d8cbb85096617", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/40dca6da36f8017429dd066ec6b95c84f302d296e8b42bfb923399c4d9c99776", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/U5FUHXIP", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/U5FUHXIP", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/7b552b556203284dce7a136935d07195!/b261277-263707", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/26f7ce5dd404e33c6570edd4ba250d20", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "37", "pages": "13959-13964", "title": "Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences", "volume": "105"}, "alternate_i